    "narrative": "The Austin Waves face a challenging slate today, navigating a gauntlet of high-end arms that depress ceiling expectations across the board. The clear cornerstone of our lineup is **Jackson Merrill** (75.27), who benefits from a prime matchup against Feltner; his status is elevated by an elite 14% park factor and a 15% boost from Feltner\u2019s profile, making him our only true anchor in a sea of marginal scores. While **Kyle Tucker** (52.03) and **Drake Baldwin** (60.73) provide necessary stability, both are contending with difficult SP matchups. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (56.38) remains a vital asset, as his dynamic platoon advantage against Ritchie offsets the pitcher\u2019s skill, securing his spot despite the inherent risks of facing a 2.57 xERA arm.\n\nOur bench decisions were dictated by a strict adherence to the 40-point efficiency floor, which unfortunately left **Josh Jung** (39.89) on the outside looking in. While **Josh Jung** showed promise, his profile against Chandler did not quite reach the threshold to displace our current starters. We are managing significant roster gaps today, with **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Gunnar Henderson** sidelined due to team off-days, and **Jordan Westburg** remains on the IL. We are also keeping a close eye on the volatility surrounding **Luis Robert Jr.** (42.06) and **Marcell Ozuna** (43.30); both are skating thin lines against top-tier arms like Ryan and deGrom. While their stolen base and power potentials keep them active, their floors are brittle today. We must remain disciplined with these game caps, as the limited upside across the rest of our roster\u2014including **Dominic Smith**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Andy Pages**, and **Heliot Ramos**\u2014leaves us little room for error if these high-xERA opponents dominate the early innings.",
